Hey <@U079YAP4R5Y>,
You can put this
`&lt;link rel="shortcut icon" href="{{ branding_favicon }}" /&gt;`
in your layout.html/base.html of the whole theme or - if you would like to change it per template(like the home has favicon A, the blog has favicon B) do it like this:

base.html/layout.html
```&lt;head&gt;
...
{% block favicon %}
&lt;link rel="shortcut icon" href="{{ brand_settings.primaryFavicon.src }}" /&gt;
{% endblock favicon %}
...
&lt;/head&gt;```
blog-listing.html
```&lt;!--
    templateType: blog_listing
    isAvailableForNewContent: true
    label: Blog listing
--&gt;
{% extends '../layouts/base.html' %}

{% block favicon %}
&lt;link rel="shortcut icon" href="{{ brand_settings.favicons[1].src }}" /&gt;
{% endblock favicon %}
...```
You would also need to add a second/third/fourth... favicon in your brandkit(HubSpot settings -&gt; Account Defaults -&gt; Branding -&gt; BRANDKIT-NAME).

Here's the guide on <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/building-blocks/module-theme-fields/branding-settings-inheritance#favicons|favicon brand inheritance >
